	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus. MRR I.401-2, Itgenshorst no. 196, Rich no. 195." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9829> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9829" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/23> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9828> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9828" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/23> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9804> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9804" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/16> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 223" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8438> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8438" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 731" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8329> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8329" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 201 and 200. They probably went on to Syria and Egypt to complete their mission by late 200 or early 199 (Iustin. 30.3.3-4; cf. Polyb. 16.27.5, and 34.2; Liv. 31.18.1, cf. 2..3-4; 33.19.8; cf. Holleaux, REA 15 [1913] 4, notes 1 and 2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2915> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2915" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "P. Cornelius Scipio Nasica succeeded M. Aemilius Lepidus as pontifex maximus. Liv. Per. 48." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2607> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2607" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected to assign unoccupied lands in Liguria and Gaul to individual settlers, ten iugera each to Romans, three each to Latins (Liv. 42.4.3-4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2541> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2541" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 458f.; Obseq. 10; Chr. 354; Oros. 4.20.34; Cassiod.; and on Lepidus, Cic. Prov. Cons. 20; Val. Max.{402} 4.2.1; 6.6.1; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc. Both consuls campaigned in Liguria and celebrated triumphs (Act. Tr. Cap. and Urbisalv., Degrassi 80f., 338f., 555; cf. Liv. 41.19.1-2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2523> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2523" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Founded the citizen colony of Luna (Liv. 41.13.4-5; cf. Salmon, CQ 27 [1933] 30-35)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2472> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2472" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f. These two enemies became publicly reconciled upon being elected (Liv. 40.45.6-46.16; Cic. Prov. Cons. 20; Val. Max. 4.2.1; Gell. 12.8.5-6; cf. Varro in Fest. 358 L, app. crit.). They instituted taxes and made changes in the tribal assembly (Liv. 40.51.9). Their building activity was notable, and especially the Basilica Aemilia et Fulvia in the Forum (Varro LL 6.4; Liv. 40.46.16, and 51-52; cf. Grueber, CRRBM 2.291; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.193ff.; Plut. Caes. 29.3). They appointed Lepidus Princeps Senatus (Liv. 40.51.1). See also Cato in FOR 1.189; Cic. De Or. 2.287." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2465> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2465" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Fulvius Flaccus succeeded C. Servilius Geminus as pontifex. M. Aemilius Lepidus succeeded C. Servilius Geminus as pontifex maximus. Cf. Val. Max. 6.6.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2380> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2380" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to found Mutina and Parma (Liv. 39.55.7-8). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 8; Münzer, APF 117." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2289> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2289" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 38.42.2; 39.6.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 454f.; Val. Max. 6.6.3; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 9.21; and on Lepidus, Polyb. 22.3.2; CIL 1\n     .2.617-620. Both Consuls were assigned to Liguria which they actively ravaged (Liv. 38.42.8-12; 39.1.1-2, and{368} 2.1-11). Lepidus was instructed to restore their arms to the Cenomani, who had been unjustly disarmed by Furius (see Praetors; Liv. 39.3.1-3), and built the Via Aemilia (Liv. 39.2.10; Strabo 5.1.11; cf. CIL 1(2).2.617-620). Flaminius reduced the Friniates and the Apuani, and built a road from Bononia to Arretium (Liv. 39.1.1-2, and 2.1-6).\n     \n      1" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2208> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2208" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "As he was criticized late in this year for leaving his province without permission of the Senate in order to sue for office, he probably continued in command of at least part of Sicily (Liv. 37.47.6; see 191, Praetors, and above, on Fabius Labeo)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2171> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2171" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Was instructed to retain his predecessor Valerius Tappo and divide his province with him if it seemed advantageous (Liv. 36.2.10-12). Cf. 37.47.6.{353}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2170> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2170" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election 35.24.6 Provinces and armies Liv. 36.2.6-15." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2128> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2128" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 35.10.11-12. Paullus was elected over twelve competitors (Plut. Aem. 3.1). See CIL 1\n     .1, p. 194- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.81." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1983> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1983" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "M. Aemilius Lepidus succeeded Ser. Sulpicius Galba." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1982> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1982" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 32.7.15." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1943> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1943" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This embassy went to various points in Greece, including Athens, then to Rhodes, and finally to Egypt (Polyb. 16.25-27; Liv. 31.18.1; App. Mac. 4). Aemilius bore Rome's ultimatum to Philip at Abydos (Polyb. 16.34.1-7; Liv. 31.18.1-7; Diod. 28.6; Iustin. 31.3.3-4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1919> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1919" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This embassy, sent ostensibly to Egypt, was appointed after Attalus of Pergamum and Rhodes had appealed to Rome regarding Philip's aggressions, and before the Consuls of 201 had returned from their provinces (Liv. 31.2.1-4, and 18.1; Polyb. 16.27, and 34.1-7; cf. Val. Max. 6.6.1; Tac. Ann. 2.67; App. Mac. 4; Iustin. 30.3-4; 31.1-2; and on the coins referring to Lepidus as tutor regis, Grueber, CRRBM 1.449; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.173f.). See 200, Legates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1918> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1918" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This embassy was appointed late in the consular year 201, as the annalistic source in Livy states, and is found active in Greece by the spring of the Julian year 200 (Holleaux, CAH 8.161; REA 25 [1923] 355f.; on the state of the Roman calendar, see De Sanctis 4.1.368ff.). They appeared in Athens in the spring of 200. Whatever may have been said about Egypt, their chief{323} mission lay in Greece, Rhodes, and Pergamum (see Walbank and McDonald, J RS 27 [1937] 189ff., and the studies discussed there; Walbank, Philip V of Macedon 313ff.). The connections between Aemilius Lepidus and the Ptolemies may have developed later (see Otto, Zur Gesch. d. Zeit d. 6. Ptolemäers, 27ff.; cf. Cichorius, RS 22f.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/9673> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #9673" ;
